headline: Tractor Supply (TSCO) Margin Dip Reinforces Cautious Investor Sentiment Despite Premium Valuation
summary: Tractor Supply (TSCO) posted earnings growth forecasts of 8.9% per year and revenue growth of 6.8% annually, both trailing the broader US market. The company’s net profit margin slipped to 7.2% from 7.7% last year. Recent results included a period of negative earnings growth, despite achieving an average annual earnings increase of 7% over the past five years. The share price sits above the estimated fair value. The market appears to be factoring in positive expectations amid modest growth...

headline: TSCO Q3 Deep Dive: Store Growth, Strategic Investments, and Category Expansion Shape Outlook
summary: Rural goods retailer Tractor Supply (NASDAQ:TSCO) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 7.2% year on year to $3.72 billion. Its GAAP profit of $0.49 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Morning Movers: Tesla, IBM slipping following quarterly reports
summary: Stock futures were modestly lower as disappointing quarterly results from major tech names weighed on sentiment. Markets look set to open with a muted tone, reflecting a mix of elevated risk and uncertainty. Oil surged nearly 4% after the U.S. imposed fresh sanctions on Russia’s top oil companies, creating a shockwave across energy markets and raising inflation concerns. Concurrently, the dollar firmed against major currencies ahead of a delayed U.S. consumer-price report, while the yen weakened
